OL,3,CNot drinking enough water causes
OL,4,Cstronger response to stress, study
OL,5,Cshows
OL,7,FProfessor Walsh said: "We know that
OL,8,Fpeople who have a low daily fluid
OL,9,Fintake, who don't meet the
OL,10,Frecommendations, are likely to be
OL,11,Fpoorly hydrated.
OL,13,F"But what we didn't know was whether,
OL,14,Fwhen you then stress those people
OL,15,Funder controlled conditions, they
OL,16,Fwould have a greater stress hormone
OL,17,Fresponse."
OL,19,FResearchers collected saliva samples
OL,20,Ffrom the group before and after the
OL,21,Fstress test to measure cortisol levels.
